  "text": "The LLVM Pass Manager registration and execution chain follows this architecture:\n\n1. PASS REGISTRATION:\n   - Pass names and creation functions are registered in llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def using macro-based definitions like MODULE_PASS(\"name\", CreatePassInstance())\n   - Each pass registers itself through PassRegistry::registerPass() in llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp\n   - The PassRegistry class (llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h) maintains a central registry storing PassInfo objects indexed by type ID and name string\n\n2. PASSMANAGER TEMPLATE:\n   - The PassManager template is defined in llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h with three parameters: IRUnitT (e.g., Module, Function), AnalysisManagerT, and ExtraArgTs\n   - The addPass<PassT>() method (lines 193-214 in PassManager.h) wraps each pass in a PassModel and stores it in a vector of PassConceptT pointers\n   - The template uses concept-based polymorphism to handle passes of different types uniformly\n   - Specialized typedef templates include ModulePassManager and FunctionPassManager for common use cases\n\n3. PIPELINE CONSTRUCTION:\n   - PassBuilder class (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h) orchestrates the construction of standard optimization pipelines\n   - buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp:1730) is the main entry point for creating complete pipelines\n   - It internally calls buildModuleSimplificationPipeline() followed by buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()\n\n4. EXECUTION ORDER FOR O2/O3:\n   - buildModuleSimplificationPipeline() (line 1091 in PassBuilderPipelines.cpp) adds early cleanup passes including:\n     * InferFunctionAttrsPass, CoroEarlyPass for setup\n     * FunctionPassManager with EntryExitInstrumenterPass, LowerExpectIntrinsicPass, SimplifyCFGPass, SROAPass, EarlyCSEPass\n     * At O3 level (line 1151): CallSiteSplittingPass is added\n   \n   - buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() (line 1478 in PassBuilderPipelines.cpp) adds aggressive optimizations including:\n     * At O3 level (line 1565): ControlHeightReductionPass\n     * LoopRotatePass, LoopDeletionPass for loop optimization\n     * Loop vectorization passes via addVectorPasses()\n     * LoopSinkPass, InstSimplifyPass, DivRemPairsPass for final simplifications\n\n5. EXECUTION:\n   - PassManager::run() is implemented in llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h (line 28)\n   - It iterates through the Passes vector sequentially (line 67)\n   - Each pass's run() method is called with the IR unit and analysis manager\n   - Analysis manager invalidates results based on PreservedAnalyses returned by each pass (line 80)\n   - Pass instrumentation callbacks are invoked before and after each pass for profiling/debugging\n\n6. OPTIMIZATION LEVELS:\n   - OptimizationLevel is defined in llvm/include/llvm/Passes/OptimizationLevel.h with static instances O0-Oz\n   - Different level combinations enable/disable specific passes:\n     * O0: Minimal optimization\n     * O1-O3: Increasing levels of optimization aggressiveness\n     * Os/Oz: Size-optimized variants\n   - Optimization level is passed through the entire pipeline construction (OptimizationLevel parameter)\n\nThe chain creates a modular, type-safe system where passes are registered once in PassRegistry.def, then dynamically composed into pipelines via PassBuilder methods, added to PassManagers via the template-based addPass() mechanism, and finally executed in sequence with automatic analysis invalidation management."
}

